running tests 
-------------

    # by directory
    pytest tests

    # by module file name
    pytest test_some_module.py
    pytest path/to/some/file.py

    # by node ids
    pytest path/to/some/file.py::test_some_function
    pytest path/to/some/file.py::TestClass::test_method

    # by keyword
    pytest -k "MyClass and not method"

    # by marker expressions
    pytest -m slow
    pytest -m "not webtest"

    # from packages. This will import `pkg.testing` and use its 
    # filesystem location to find and run tests.
    pytest --pyargs pkg.testing

- stopping after first failure

    pytest -x tests

- turn off output capture (i.e. show output)

    pytest -s 

- stopping after 2 failures

    pytest --maxfail=2 tests

- pdb

    # drop to pdb on every failures
    pytest --pdb

    # drop to pdb after first failure
    pytest -x --pdb tests

    # drop to pdb for first 3 failures
    pytest --maxfail=3 --pdb tests

    on any failure the exception information is stored in `sys.last_value`, `sys.last_type` and `sys.last_traceback`
